/susan-vahabzadeh">Susan Vahabzadeh</a></dt><dd>Germany</dd><dt><a href="/sight-and-sound/greatest-films-all-time/all-voters/jessica-winter">Jessica Winter</a></dt><dd>USA</dd></dl></section><section><h3>Directors</h3><dl><dt><a href="/sight-and-sound/greatest-films-all-time/all-voters/paul-bush">Paul Bush</a></dt><dd>UK</dd><dt><a href="/sight-and-sound/greatest-films-all-time/all-voters/anurag-kashyap">Anurag Kashyap</a></dt><dd>India</dd><dt><a href="/sight-and-sound/greatest-films-all-time/all-voters/nina-menkes">Nina Menkes</a></dt><dd>USA</dd><dt><a href="/sight-and-sound/greatest-films-all-time/all-voters/paul-schrader">Paul Schrader</a></dt><dd>US</dd></dl></section></div></details><div class="ArticleGrid__Outer-sc-nctj0m-0 iIGxlL article_grid_block"><h2 class="Headline__H2-sc-e1fxl5-2 eKkqcD ArticleGrid__StyledHeadline-sc-nctj0m-3 dQGFXG" aria-label="">Articles related to Metropolis</h2><div class="ArticleGrid__Articles-sc-nctj0m-1 hNktDT withBackground"><article uuid="51508bac-8436-48bc-a84c-0608040afa26" image48x27="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2020-08/fritz-lang-portrait-eyepatch-looking-at-camera-california-1967.jpg/96x54-cropped/fritz-lang-portrait-eyepatch-looking-at-camera-california-1967.jpg" standfirst="Fritz Lang, the towering figure of German cinema’s golden era, talks to critic and biographer Axel Madsen about his life and times, and his long career in Germany, France and Hollywood." class="ArticleCard__Outer-sc-zrtbni-0 eIZIIS articleCard Interviews"><div class="ArticleCard__CategoryTag-sc-zrtbni-7 yMPPW">From the Sight and Sound archive</div><div class="ArticleCard__PageImageContainer-sc-zrtbni-5 ehvIXQ"><div class="ArticleCard__PageImage-sc-zrtbni-6 iRumHQ image"></div></div><h3 class="ArticleCard__Heading-sc-zrtbni-3 bynrVe">A man for all seasons: Fritz Lang interviewed in 1967</h3><div class="ArticleCard__Meta-sc-zrtbni-1 edgoES"><p class="ArticleCard__Author-sc-zrtbni-2 KIAzD">By Axel Madsen</p><